Section 1:
SR 36 Text skip navigation SENATE PRESIDENT SENATORS COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS SENATE CLERK SENATE RULES HOUSE SPEAKER DELEGATES COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS HOUSE CLERK HOUSE RULES HOUSE STAFF JOINT INTERIM COMMITTEES LEGISLATIVE ADMINISTRATOR LEGISLATIVE SERVICES DIVISION PUBLIC INFORMATION LEGISLATIVE AUTOMATED SYSTEMS DIVISION LEGISLATIVE AUDITOR'S OFFICE PERFORMANCE EVALUATION & RESEARCH DIVISION POST AUDIT DIVISION BUDGET DIVISION REGULATORY AND FISCAL AFFAIRS DIVISION CLAIMS COMMISSION CRIME VICTIMS RULE-MAKING REVIEW SPECIAL INVESTIGATIONS JUDICIAL COMP. COMMISSION JOINT RULES STAFF INFO BILL STATUS BILL STATUS BILL TRACKING STATE LAW WEST VIRGINIA CODE ACTS OF THE LEGISLATURE CODE OF 1931 WV CONSTITUTION US CONSTITUTION REPORTS AGENCY REPORTS AGENCY GRANT AWARDS PERFORMANCE EVALUATIONS POST AUDITS EDUCATIONAL CITIZEN’S GUIDE INTERNSHIP PROGRAM PAGE PROGRAM PUBLICATIONS PHOTO GALLERY CAPITOL HISTORY HOW A BILL BECOMES LAW CONTACT SENATE ROSTER HOUSE ROSTER PUBLIC INFO. NEWS RELEASES HELPFUL LINKS Introduced Version Senate Resolution 36 History |  Email Key: Green = existing Code. Red = new code to be enacted SENATE RESOLUTION 36(By Senators Deeds, Woelfel, Rucker, Rose, and Helton)[Introduced March 18, 2025] Recognizing the 100th anniversary of the State Fair of West Virginia.Whereas, The State Fair of West Virginia is celebrating its 100th anniversary on March 19, 2025; andWhereas, The State Fair of West Virginia was established on March 19, 1921, as the Greenbrier Valley Fair, and then on March 19, 1941, was renamed the State Fair of West Virginia; andWhereas, The mission of the State Fair of West Virginia is to honor our heritage through programs and events that promote the traditions of agriculture, education, and family entertainment; andWhereas, The State Fair of West Virginia strives to host quality, nationally recognized fair events and to develop non-fair events that create opportunities for community engagement, and to support the youth and community through educational programs; andWhereas, The State Fair of West Virginia had to cancel its annual fair only four times in its history due to WWII in 1941, 1942, 1944, and 1945, and again in 2020, due to the Covid-19 pandemic; andWhereas, The State Fair of West Virginia’s annual economic impact to the state is $16.9 million, with $2.5 million in generated tax revenue.  It is also one of the state’s top retailers in lottery sales with $1 million generated; andWhereas, The State Fair of West Virginia employs over 150 employees during the 10-dayevent with a payroll of over $250,000; andWhereas, Each year $20,000 is given in scholarships to students from West Virginia to attend colleges, universities, or trade programs equaling over a half million dollars in scholarships; andWhereas, Over $65,000 is paid to non-profit, civic, or school groups for services performed during the fair, with over 200 independent concessionaires/vendors; andWhereas, It is ranked as one of the top agriculturally based fairs in the country with over 400 WV 4-H and FFA livestock exhibitors, and 800 total exhibitors; andWhereas, Over $200,000 is awarded every year in premiums for livestock, 4-H and projects, and the home, arts, and garden department. Youth Livestock Auctions totaled $450,000 which goes directly back to each youth participant and has brought in over $4 million since 2013; andWhereas, Twenty state agencies are represented during the fair, one of which includes the Department of Agriculture’s WV Grown store along with national artists that are booked on the grandstand each year; therefore, be itResolved by the Senate:That the Senate hereby recognizes the 100th anniversary of the State Fair of West Virginia; and, be itFurther resolved, That the Senate recognizes the economic impact the State Fair of West Virginia has provided for 100 years along with the opportunities provided to the community and the state; and, be itFurther Resolved, That the Clerk is hereby directed to forward a copy of this resolution to Kelly Collins, CEO, State Fair of West Virginia. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone:


