e youth and community through educational programs; andWhereas, The State Fair of West Virginia had to cancel its annual fair only four times in its history due to WWII in 1941, 1942, 1944, and 1945, and again in 2020, due to the Covid-19 pandemic; andWhereas, The State Fair of West Virginia’s annual economic impact to the state is $16.9 million, with $2.5 million in generated tax revenue.  It is also one of the state’s top retailers in lottery sales with $1 million generated; andWhereas, The State Fair of West Virginia employs over 150 employees during the 10-dayevent with a payroll of over $250,000; andWhereas, Each year $20,000 is given in scholarships to students from West Virginia to attend colleges, universities, or trade programs equaling over a half million dollars in scholarships; andWhereas, Over $65,000 is paid to non-profit, civic, or school groups for services performed during the fair, with over 200 independent concessionaires/vendors; andWhereas, It is ranked as one of the top agriculturally based fairs in the country with over 400 WV 4-H and FFA livestock exhibitors, and 800 total exhibitors; andWhereas, Over $200,000 is awarded every year in premiums for livestock, 4-H and projects, and the home, arts, and garden department. Youth Livestock Auctions totaled $450,000 which goes directly back to each youth participant and has brought in over $4 million since 2013; andWhereas, Twenty state agencies are represented during the fair, one of which includes the Department of Agriculture’s WV Grown store along with national artists that are booked on the grandstand each year; therefore, be itResolved by the Senate:That the Senate hereby recognizes the 100th anniversary of the State Fair of West Virginia; and, be itFurther resolved, That the Senate recognizes the economic impact the State Fair of West Virginia has provided for 100 years along with the opportunities provided to the community and the state; and, be itFurther Resolved, That the Clerk is hereby directed to forward a copy of this resolution to Kelly Collins, CEO, State Fair of West Virginia. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone: